This paper discusses the integration of various theories, including a prescriptive theory of uncertainty, to solve a class of problems called Dynamic Classification Problem. This problem requires a supporting reasoning system, which involves knowledge engineering, rule cross-compiler, and real-time inference engine with meta-reasoning capabilities. These topics are closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), software engineering (cs.SE), programming languages (cs.PL), and computer engineering (cs.CE). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
